==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forby
<hw>For*by"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv. & prep.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Foreby</er>.]</ety> <def>Near; hard by; along; past.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To tell her if her child went ought <qex>forby</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the intent that ships may pass along <qex>forby</qex> all the
sides of the city without let.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's
Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forcarve</ent>⟦br⟧
